                                &lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;poster AGU 2010&#34; src=&#34;/media/images/paoloAGU2010.png&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This poster was made using &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.latex-project.org/&#34;&gt;LaTeX&lt;/a&gt; with the &lt;a href=&#34;http://www-i6.informatik.rwth-aachen.de/~dreuw/latexbeamerposter.php&#34;&gt;Beamerposter&lt;/a&gt; package. I&amp;#8217;ve modified one of the default themes to my own needs (and taste). If you are interested in using (and modifying) this template you can download the tarball with the LaTeX source code and&amp;nbsp;figures:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://quakeinfo.ucsd.edu/~fpaolo/files/paoloAGU2010.tar.bz2&#34;&gt;paoloAGU2010.tar.bz2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://quakeinfo.ucsd.edu/~fpaolo/files/paoloAGU2010.pdf&#34;&gt;paoloAGU2010.pdf&lt;/a&gt; (81&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&#34;caps&#34;&gt;MB&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To generate a &lt;span class=&#34;caps&#34;&gt;PDF&lt;/span&gt; poster first decompress the&amp;nbsp;tarball:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;codehilite&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nv&#34;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;tar xjf paoloAGU2010.tar.bz2
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;and then compile the source&amp;nbsp;code:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;codehilite&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nv&#34;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;cd &lt;/span&gt;paoloAGU2010    
&lt;span class=&#34;nv&#34;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;pdflatex paoloAGU2010.tex
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;That&amp;#8217;s&amp;nbsp;all!&lt;/p&gt;            </content>
